A BIN lorry has careered into the front garden of a Glasgow house after the driver took ill at the wheel.
 The  Glasgow City Council truck crashed around 11am at Croftside Avenue, near King's Park in Glasgow. 
Emergency services were called to the scene where they found the driver unwell.
 
Breaking story...Glasgow City Council bin lorry crashes into a house in Kings Park area. No one hit by the truck. pic.twitter.com/MUjvnSptMi

He was taken to the city's Victoria Infirmary.
Nobody else was hurt during the incident.
